cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.DS 

The paper discusses hashing techniques for visual data and their application in large-scale databases such as online images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new performance metric for hashing-based retrieval, which involves mathematical analysis and experimentation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
